WEBVTT

00:02.461 --> 00:04.247
MOHINDER:
Previously on Heroes.

00:04.630 --> 00:07.337
I'm not gonna let you
manipulate me. I'm the one
making the decisions.

00:07.425 --> 00:10.041
Mr. Petrelli,
you're playing yourself?

00:10.136 --> 00:11.797
I'm obviously
playing Mister...

00:11.929 --> 00:15.638
She can't see me,
Nathan. No one can.
Exceptyou.

00:15.766 --> 00:16.755
You're different.

00:17.018 --> 00:18.053
You're special.

00:18.144 --> 00:20.760
My name is Daphne.
And why are you two
following me?

00:20.855 --> 00:21.970
I want my father's
formula back.

00:22.064 --> 00:24.851
DAPHNE: There's supposed to be
some sort of exchange
going down at this theater,

00:24.942 --> 00:26.648
and I'm waiting
to intercept.

00:27.987 --> 00:30.945
You were right.
lam just a killer.

00:31.949 --> 00:35.487
I guess you were
wrong about me.
We'll see.

00:35.620 --> 00:38.202
You wanna tell me
that's not you?
It's not me.

00:38.289 --> 00:39.529
(PANTING)
You can't run this story.

00:40.208 --> 00:41.197
(GROANS)

00:43.127 --> 00:44.116
(GASPS)

00:45.296 --> 00:48.038
My name is Tracy Strauss.
Do you know me?

00:48.299 --> 00:49.334
Know you?

00:49.467 --> 00:50.752
| created you.

00:50.843 --> 00:53.220
PETER: ...to find you,
get you out of here.

00:53.471 --> 00:54.802
I need to show you.

00:55.640 --> 00:57.301
The whole world
is in trouble.

00:57.600 --> 01:00.012
MOHINDER: Reflexes,
blood pressure, balance.

01:00.102 --> 01:03.720
They're all normal.
I'm completely
the same in every way.

01:04.232 --> 01:05.438
Just different.

01:08.653 --> 01:10.109
MAYA: My God.

01:11.447 --> 01:12.983
(MAN SHOUTING)

01:18.663 --> 01:20.324
(WOMAN SHOUTING)

01:23.417 --> 01:24.497
(REWINDING)

01:24.585 --> 01:27.793
MOHINDER:
This is Dr. Mohinder Suresh.
Journal entry 12.

01:27.880 --> 01:30.667
Three days after
injecting the genetic
modification formula.

01:30.758 --> 01:34.376
My reflexes are sharper,
my strength off the charts.

01:34.470 --> 01:36.301
It’s a dream come true.

01:36.430 --> 01:39.672
Who among us hasn’t
wished for strength?
To fly?

01:39.767 --> 01:42.349
And now
it’s all possible.

01:43.020 --> 01:44.009
(BEEPS)

01:45.773 --> 01:47.809
There are a few
adverse reactions.

01:47.900 --> 01:51.984
The one exception
being an unusual rash.

01:52.154 --> 01:54.531
A by-product
of the formula?
An allergy?

01:54.615 --> 01:55.695
(CRASHING)

01:55.783 --> 01:58.320
WOMAN: God, no!
Please, don't... Stop it!

01:58.411 --> 02:00.823
Hello?
Is everything all right?

02:02.081 --> 02:05.073
I'm sorry to intrude, but
I heard shouting and I wanted
to make sure everything...

02:05.167 --> 02:08.079
Everything's fine.
Thanks.

02:08.587 --> 02:10.839
Are you sure?
'Cause it looks
like your wife...

02:10.923 --> 02:14.916
She'll be fine.
Now back off, sahib.

02:16.637 --> 02:17.968
(GROANS)

02:18.055 --> 02:21.673
(CRYING) Stop it! Stop it!
Stop it! Stop! Please.

02:21.767 --> 02:24.258
Just leave us alone,
all right?

02:26.230 --> 02:27.891
God, don't hurt him.

02:32.153 --> 02:35.361
You were one of three
identical triplets.

02:35.448 --> 02:40.033
Tracy, Niki and Barbara.
Perfect test subjects.

02:40.119 --> 02:45.705
When your birth parents died,
we separated you, we...

02:45.791 --> 02:48.077
| just need some answers.

02:49.086 --> 02:50.667
What did you do to me?

02:50.755 --> 02:52.746
DNA manipulation.

02:52.882 --> 02:55.965
A formula that would
make you incredible.

02:56.260 --> 02:58.216
Speed. Strength.

02:59.472 --> 03:02.464
Is it something
like that?

03:08.481 --> 03:09.596
VVhy?

03:10.941 --> 03:12.852
Why would you do this?

03:14.278 --> 03:15.859
What gave you the right?

03:15.946 --> 03:17.152
We had no right.

03:17.823 --> 03:21.361
We were arrogant
and selfish and human.

03:21.452 --> 03:22.692
Who? Who wanted this?

03:22.787 --> 03:25.904
I think I've said
too much already.

03:25.998 --> 03:27.989
They would not like that.

03:28.084 --> 03:29.665
Give me a name.

03:31.212 --> 03:32.497
Someone.

03:33.130 --> 03:37.123
There was a company.
A company that...

03:37.802 --> 03:40.794
l... I don't remember.
I can't remember.

03:40.971 --> 03:42.586
You're lying.

03:42.681 --> 03:45.263
They made us forget.

03:45.601 --> 03:47.557
Well, then,
you have to
take it away.

03:47.645 --> 03:51.308
This thing that I can do.
I can't.

03:51.399 --> 03:53.310
No, you don't understand.

03:53.526 --> 03:57.064
This ability...
l've hurt people.

03:57.988 --> 03:59.194
It is part of you.

03:59.281 --> 04:01.112
No, I never asked for it.

04:01.200 --> 04:03.862
You need
to take it away.
I can't.

04:03.953 --> 04:07.320
Tell me how
to take it away.
Tell me how...

04:07.415 --> 04:08.404
(MOANS)

04:13.379 --> 04:15.085
I'm so sorry.

04:15.339 --> 04:16.875
What have you done?

04:18.592 --> 04:21.004
Who is she?
What happened to her?

04:21.220 --> 04:24.587
It's your future,
Parkman, not mine.

04:26.225 --> 04:29.592
Yeah, it is. So that means
that I can stop that
from happening, right?

04:29.687 --> 04:31.894
You really want to know?

04:37.361 --> 04:40.353
This stuff is supposed
to show me my future?

04:41.574 --> 04:42.563
(FLIES BUZZING)

04:42.658 --> 04:43.898
(EXCLAIMS IN DISGUST)

04:45.911 --> 04:47.572
I don't think
this is working.

04:48.664 --> 04:52.077
Here, try this.

05:27.828 --> 05:29.329
(SIREN WAlLlNG)

05:30.122 --> 05:31.362
Come on.

05:32.208 --> 05:34.995
Where are we?
When are we?

05:35.085 --> 05:36.825
This is the future
I came back to stop.

05:36.921 --> 05:39.253
Why? It looks
just like today.

05:41.050 --> 05:43.917
With one big difference.

05:44.011 --> 05:45.046
MAN: All right.
I'll see you.

05:56.273 --> 05:58.059
How is this possible?

05:58.150 --> 06:00.641
An injection.
Abilities are available
to anyone.

06:00.736 --> 06:03.853
For sale if you can
afford it, for grabs
if you're desperate enough.

06:03.948 --> 06:07.566
But all these people
with abilities are going
to destroy the world.

06:08.744 --> 06:10.609
How could you know that?
How would you?

06:10.704 --> 06:12.786
l've painted it.
Dreamed it.

06:12.873 --> 06:14.784
It's going to happen.
Here, look.

06:15.626 --> 06:17.958
All the crime,
murder, all abilities.

06:18.128 --> 06:21.962
People can't be trusted.
We're weak. Jealous. Violent.

06:22.091 --> 06:23.456
There's always
good people. Always.

06:23.551 --> 06:27.214
How could I be so naive?
No, abilities are
the new weapon of choice.

06:27.304 --> 06:29.716
People will control
themselves.

06:31.308 --> 06:34.141
It's not safe for me
to be out in the open.
They'll be looking for us.

06:34.228 --> 06:35.718
I needed you to see.

06:35.813 --> 06:38.054
Who are they?
What did you do?

06:38.148 --> 06:42.642
They think I'm an extremist.
A villain. I had to stop it.

06:42.820 --> 06:45.812
Maybe they're right.
You shot Nathan.
You killed him.

06:45.990 --> 06:47.821
He was going
to tell everyone
the truth about us.

06:47.950 --> 06:50.316
But he didn't die.
And now he doesn't have to.

06:50.452 --> 06:53.319
So, why hasn't
everything changed?

06:53.497 --> 06:55.579
Look, someone
from your time is
putting together

06:55.666 --> 06:58.373
a formula that gives
people abilities.

06:58.502 --> 07:00.584
You have to stop him.
Why me?
Why can't you do it?

07:00.671 --> 07:02.832
Because I made
terrible choices.

07:04.341 --> 07:06.002
Stepped on
too many
butterflies.

07:06.176 --> 07:10.089
What does that mean?
You can't make
the same mistakes as me.

07:10.514 --> 07:11.674
We need to find Sylar.

07:11.807 --> 07:14.423
With his ability,
you won't make
the same mistakes.

07:14.518 --> 07:18.727
Sylar? What the hell are you
talking about? I want to
see Nathan. Claire. Suresh.

07:18.856 --> 07:21.939
They're not the people
you think they are.
Why not?

07:22.026 --> 07:25.439
Not all of us were born
with abilities, okay?
Some of us were made.

07:25.613 --> 07:28.480
A line was drawn.
Sides were chosen.
lt tore us apart.

07:28.574 --> 07:29.734
(GUNSHOTS)

07:34.622 --> 07:36.032
Claire?

07:36.874 --> 07:37.989
(PETER EXCLAIMS)

07:38.083 --> 07:40.039
(GUNSHOTS)

07:42.880 --> 07:43.869
(GROANS)

08:14.286 --> 08:15.275
(EXCLAIMS)

08:15.996 --> 08:19.238
You actually did it.
You killed Peter.

08:19.333 --> 08:22.825
No. He's still alive.

08:23.253 --> 08:25.915
Looks plenty dead to me.
There were two of them.

08:26.048 --> 08:28.585
This one
and a younger one
from the past.

08:28.717 --> 08:31.834
This is bad, right?
Bad,bad.

08:31.929 --> 08:34.887
Now we have our orders.
Kill Petrelli.

08:34.973 --> 08:36.634
That's obviously
easier said than done.

08:36.767 --> 08:38.598
We need to use Molly.

08:39.478 --> 08:42.436
She can find Peter
anywhere in the world.

08:43.774 --> 08:45.514
You know
I can't just do that.

08:45.609 --> 08:47.725
It's not that simple.
It is.

08:47.945 --> 08:50.903
If you won't ask her,
I will.

08:53.242 --> 08:56.450
I'm not afraid of you.
No, but you are
afraid of Peter.

08:56.578 --> 08:59.536
And you know
he won't stop,
not ever.

08:59.623 --> 09:01.363
Until we find him.

09:02.626 --> 09:04.287
And we kill him.

09:09.299 --> 09:15.010
(PANTING) Let me out!
I must save the world!
The future depends on it!

09:17.349 --> 09:18.338
(GROANS)

09:18.976 --> 09:20.637
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

09:33.407 --> 09:34.988
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

09:37.494 --> 09:39.280
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

09:39.621 --> 09:41.236
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

10:24.124 --> 10:25.785
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

10:25.876 --> 10:27.491
Senator Petrelli?

10:29.546 --> 10:32.003
Senator, you need
to make a choice.

10:32.090 --> 10:34.547
There are
a lot of historical
desks available.

10:34.843 --> 10:37.459
Where's Tracy?
Isn't it herjob to
make these decisions?

10:37.554 --> 10:40.216
Miss Strauss isn't
answering her cell.

10:41.183 --> 10:44.300
Take the John Foster Dulles.
It sends the right message.

10:44.394 --> 10:45.975
Which one would you pick?

10:47.564 --> 10:50.351
Robert Kennedy's.

10:50.442 --> 10:52.228
Kennedy it is.
Thank you.

10:55.823 --> 10:56.812
(DOOR CLOSING)

10:56.907 --> 10:59.990
You know, I thought
you'd be enjoying this.

11:00.077 --> 11:01.317
You're a Senator.

11:01.411 --> 11:04.494
Back in the seat of power,
where you belong.

11:04.581 --> 11:06.742
Able to do God's work
here on earth.

11:06.875 --> 11:09.412
God's work?
I'm picking out desks.

11:10.921 --> 11:13.162
What's the real problem
here, Nathan?

11:13.257 --> 11:15.669
You. You're
the real problem.

11:15.759 --> 11:18.592
You don't trust me?
I'm hurt.

11:18.679 --> 11:20.840
I'm the only one
who can see you.

11:20.931 --> 11:22.512
What, that's a problem?

11:22.599 --> 11:25.841
Don't play me, okay?
I've been around people
who can do amazing things.

11:25.936 --> 11:28.177
What are you?
What are you,
a telepath?

11:28.272 --> 11:31.355
(CHUCKLES) No,
nothing that obvious.

11:31.441 --> 11:34.683
You know what it is?
It's brain damage
from the shooting.

11:34.778 --> 11:37.941
The shooting that you
so miraculously survived.

11:38.031 --> 11:41.148
Come on, Nathan.
I mean, healing, flying.

11:41.243 --> 11:43.529
I mean, isn't that
the work of angels?

11:43.620 --> 11:45.611
So you're saying
you're an angel?

11:45.956 --> 11:47.617
You're a murderer.

11:47.708 --> 11:51.621
You wanted to destroy
New York City.
Kill millions of people.

11:51.712 --> 11:54.124
If I remember correctly,
you did, too.

11:54.214 --> 11:56.205
What exactly do you
want from me?

11:56.300 --> 11:59.588
I want to help you.
First as Senator.

12:02.055 --> 12:03.716
Then President.

12:03.807 --> 12:04.967
(LAUGHS)

12:07.811 --> 12:09.267
President?

12:09.980 --> 12:12.642
The greater the fall,
the grander the ascension.

12:12.774 --> 12:15.481
Isn't that what
you've always wanted?

12:17.905 --> 12:21.898
Trust me,
this is the path
to salvation.

12:22.326 --> 12:25.989
It's not my path,
not if you're
leading the way.

12:27.331 --> 12:28.662
(DOOR OPENING)

12:31.585 --> 12:33.746
This place is disgusting.

12:33.837 --> 12:37.671
The milk's gone bad.
Didn't you notice?

12:38.133 --> 12:40.590
Look, I don't need you
cleaning up after me.

12:40.677 --> 12:42.668
Obviously you do.

12:43.305 --> 12:44.670
(EXCLAIMS IN DISGUST)

12:45.849 --> 12:47.350
You don't look well.

12:47.434 --> 12:48.719
I'm just tired.

12:49.519 --> 12:52.010
No wonder.
Working all hours.

12:53.106 --> 12:56.519
No food,
no fresh air.
I have lots to do.

12:56.860 --> 12:59.522
Come on,
let's get out of here.
I can't.

13:01.531 --> 13:03.863
But it's a beautiful day
outside.

13:04.368 --> 13:06.108
And you've been
cooped up in here...

13:06.203 --> 13:07.283
(BANGS)

13:07.871 --> 13:12.535
Working for you!
Trying to find some way
to take away your ability!

13:13.126 --> 13:15.208
Isn't that
what you want?

13:16.505 --> 13:20.669
I came
because I care about you.
You want me to go? Fine.

13:22.678 --> 13:26.296
Wait.
I didn't mean to yell.

13:26.556 --> 13:27.591
(SlGHS)

13:27.683 --> 13:32.302
I'm just tired.
I will find the answers
for you.

13:32.938 --> 13:34.144
I promise.

13:49.746 --> 13:51.077
(BEEPS)

13:51.373 --> 13:55.036
Journal entry 13.
The rash is spreading.

13:55.544 --> 13:58.251
I don't know what it is
or its connection
to my aggression.

13:59.339 --> 14:03.002
The formula is
transforming me
and I fear...

14:04.970 --> 14:07.632
I fear what I am becoming.

14:11.560 --> 14:14.097
MOHINDER: The formula is
transforming me.

14:14.438 --> 14:15.473
(DISTORTED)
/ fear what I’m becoming.

14:15.564 --> 14:17.976
The formula
